Original_Text:
CEPA 6 200620854



				Topic A (The Worst Holiday)



Last summer, I was forced to go on a vacation to London with my family that was so horrible its beyond any description I can make of it.
The torture started right from the beginning at the airport. My father carelessly forgot our passports at home so we had to wait for forty five minutes in the crowded airport untill he drove back with them.
Additionally, since my parents were very unorganised, they expected to find our first class seats ready without any bookings. Unfortunatley, there were no more first class seats available so we were seperated in economy class.
Furthermore, all the five star hotels were occupied so we temporarily had to stay at a very low class, cheap motel with no air conditioning, in addition to the fact that I had to share a bed with my extremely unhygenic brother.
Finally I admit that that was the worst holiday I had ever been on.

The best movie I have ever seen is Man on Fire. If it was in my hand, I would’ve choosen this movie to be the award winning movie because I personally liked the movie a lot. The main idea of the movie is kidnapping and rapping the children of wealthy families in South America. The idea was mainly about a girl who’s father try to protect from kidnappers by hiring a bodyguard The main roles were played by Denzel Washington and Dakotta Fanning However, the bodyguard fails to protect the young  girl and insisted on getting the girl back to her parents without being harmed.
Shockingly Denzel Washington (Bodygaurd) discovered that the girl’s father was under the kidnapping issue of his daughter. He’ve done that to protect his wealth and money. At the end, the father was killed and Denzel Washington took the risk of trading his soul with the young girl’s soul in order to live happily with her mother.
As a personal point of view, I liked the movie’s audio and visual effects. The effect were perfectly matched with the movies message and settling. They were dark, gloomy and so dramatic.

Last summer’s vication I went to Eygpt. Eygpt is one of the greatest countries I visited in my whole life. I went with my whole family members. We had a great time due to the fantastic warm weather and off course the great place. People there are so freindly and cheerful although some of them are poor and simple but they always welcome us.
In the first day I visited the great Pyramids, they are so huge. And I saw the “ABU ALHOUL”, and I enjoyed taking pictures there with my family. The resturants there are great too, I liked the eygptian food much. One of their famous kinds of food called “Kushari” it consists of rice, tomato souce and some green vegetables. It is dilecous.

Every year, when the summer holiday comes my family and I decide together on a specific country that we would like to visit. Last summer we went to Turkey.
Visiting Turkey was a good experience; we had a great time discovering all the historical places and markets. As the eldest child; I helped my parents on planning the trip, we visited different cities in Turkey: Bolu, Borsa and Istanbul.
I played with my brothers and sister in The Istanbul Theme Park. The best thing about that vacation was that I learned a lot from it, not just about Turkey, but also about the Islamic History. Learning more about my religions history changed something in me, I became more proud of my Islamic Identity which makes me feel special amongst other people.
Summer vacation was over quickly, but it was such a blast. I had a lot of fun and learned new Interesting things. I hope next years holiday would be just as exciting.

Last summer, I went with my family to Gold Coast, Australia. I believe it was the best vacation ever. I enjoyed my time a lot andour schedule was always busy.
I visited many places such as: First, Dream World that all kinds of roller coasters. Second, Movie World, that had the most amazing shows. Third, Sea World, that had great dolphin and alligator shows.
My family and I tried many restaurants such as Chinese, Italian, and Mexican ones. But as I recall, my favourite restaurant was Peter’s Sea Food, they served the best shrimps and crabs I have ever eaten.
Over there, we stayed at the Peninsula Appartements where I met some of my friends. Every night, I used to go with them to the arcade and afterwards to drink coffee at Starbacks, which is something I liked a lot.
Finally, I do believe that this was my best vacation. I loved Australia, the weather, and the people too. My vacation way simply perfect.

It was early in the morning when both my friend and I decided to take a vacation in Turkey. We booked our flight and it was not full. We arrived at Istanbul that night. We  checked in our hotel then went out for a walk. The weather was amazing. It was just right. We sat on the side of a lake and had our dinner then headed straight back to the hotel to rest for the next day. It was at 10 am when we went to the Blu Mosque and  prayed in it. it is a very big old mosque. Aftr that we went to see another mosque however, this one was once a church. It is called “sophi”, Soon after, my friend and I headed to a coupleof museums. We saw the prophet Mohammed’s hair (peace be upon him) and the keys that opened the Kaba and also swords that belonged to soldiers in the past.
The trip was wonderful and we enjoyed it very much. It was nice to have a little holiday and the country is full of history. There were many great things we learned and new people we met. It was a holiday to remember.

Every one had a happy moments in his life such as perfect holiday. I like travelling so much specially with my family. Every vacation  summer we travel to a country .
Last summer holiday we travelled to an Arabian country that is Syria .
Syria is a very beautiful country . It is in Asia contenant. We visited there several places . 
We stayed at the capital Damuscas for a week. That is famous of it's old shops like "Al-Hamidya"  shop. It's wide and contains of many small shops.We also visited the small villages like  "Homus", " Al-lathikia" and "Tadmur". The restaurant in Syria is famous of its delicious food.
I like so much the "kabab" and the "taboola". We also visited the Central Museum in Damascus . It contains many old thing that they used in the past. The people there are so kind and helpful.
I liked them so much . It's really amazing country .
It was the best holiday in my life. I have enjoyed my time very much . I think I had many 
benifits from this holiday such as meeting different people, having look at their traditionals and knowing more places in this country, in my opinion everybody have to visit this country.

When you receive a gift, you always consider how much love a person have put into it and not how much it cost. A person ones said to me that you can see how much a person love you by the cover of his/her gift. A favourite possession for someone else maybe something that he bought according to his liking, but for me my favourites possessions are the gifts that I used to have from my friends when we were in grade 1 and 2.
A child is always happy with what is given to him, even if it is a little thing. A paper that has a nice drawing and a mispelled “I luv yo” could make him cheerful for a whole day. When I first recieved  those gift I never thought that I will keep them or treasure them for more than 10 years. I treasured those gifts as well as the person who gave them to me, because a child always to things according to his heart and my friends must have really loved me to give me such a things. Gifts also keep me from forgetting my friend even if I havent met them from a long time.
Some people may think gift as a silly thing to be considered as a favourite possession, but if prefer things that is given to me more than the things that I buy according to what I like and what I want. A gift is something given to you by another person who is full of love and caring for you, therefore a person who receives the gift should treasure it as he/she had treasured her owner, (giver of the gift).

There are many ways that can the person enjoy his free time. For us as school student the summer holiday is our dream durring the year, so we started to plan what will be going to do in summer with the beinging of the school year. last year my plan was travelling to Australia, and I have lots of dream to reach them. I told my sister and she agreed me and she liked the idea, and we started to plan how gone we tell my father. I remmeber it was lunch time when I told him, the first thing he did it, it was when he couldn’t swaly the food, his face turned red he looked so funny. After he had cup of water he said that Australia is a long journey and it takes may be 10 hours to reach the capital. I started with my sister to change his idea. He ended the conversation by saying our summer vication will be in london, I couldn’t say any thing because he was a little mad and angry. So the summer came and we travelled to london with my parents and my 2 brothers and my sister. We already had aparment there. I werent feelling interested to go to london. We dawasy had berkfast in Pret coffeshop which locatted in Oxford Street. One day we went to the royal park which it is the high park, we want there for walking it was afternoon time, I were walking with my father and watching my brother and his friend playing football. Suddly I had listened to sound, it wasn’t strang, I listtened carefully to know what kind of sound it’s it was dog breathing. I started to panic, my father tried to do some funny thing to let the dog go to him, but he didn’t move from  his place which was behined me, untill his ouner came and taked him and he apoligaise about what happened. I started crying and saying if we were in Australia you wouldn’t see a dog walking alone. They  laught at me. It was the worest holiday that I wouldn’t forget it.

Ever since I was little I enjoyed painting so much . First, I was using my bare hands and I covered them  with colors to draw. But then, when I was in the kindergarden I learned to draw with different tools like brushes and pencils.
Nowadays, I use various kinds of colors, like water colors and acrilic. I like to draw when someone with  me. It's always fun to have people around you to share the things you love. My nefew always paints with me .
We used to hang our drawings on the wall, but now we hang them on a white board which we created especially for them. I also enjoy other artistic activities like poetry. I love to write  poetry because I think it is a way of expressing our thoughts and feelings, like painting . I often write when I do not have many things to do. 
Most of my work was done in the summer holiday and it is full of optimistic and happy words. However, sometimes it contains pessimistic lines when I write about the world around us.  
Whenever I am bored, I paint or write. It's a good way of spending your spare time and I think it is important to everyone to have a useful hobby. It can protect you from doing other bad activities.

I love to write poetry because I think it is a way of expressing our thoughts and feelings, like painting . I often write when I do not have many things to do. Most of my work was done in the summer holiday and it is full of optimistic and happy words. However, sometimes it contains pessimistic lines when I write about the world around us. Whenever I am bored, I paint or write. It's a good way of spending your spare time and I think it is important to everyone to have a useful hobby. It can protect you from doing other bad activities.

Original_Text:
CEPA 6 200620358



			          “ The Perfect Holiday”


People often go to holidays to enjoy their time in certain countries. They like to believe in having a perfect holiday when they’re planning it. But have you ever had a perfect holiday? Well I have. My perfect holiday was on the 8th of August, 2005. I went on this holiday with my family. We went to France, Spain, and Italy, respectively.
When we first started on our holiday, I was so excited and enthusiastic that I researched on all of these countries and made a plan on where to go and what to see.
In France I went to Disney’s emusement park where I get to see Mickey Mouse and all his friends. I went to the Louvre’ Museum and got to see the Mona Lisa painting of Lionardo. I also went  to see the Eifel Tower, which wasn’t what I expected it to be. In Spain, I went to Spain’s old village, which luck has it, I got to see the shooting of a new american movie called “Perfume”. And in Italy, I went to the Colusium, the Treve’ Fountain,  and the Leening Tower of Pizza.
This holiday  was so perfect because I got to spend time with my family enjoying doing new things, going to exciting new places, and learning about new cultures. A perfect holiday doesn’t, only envolve going to new places, but also spending time with the ones that you love is what makes a holiday special for us.
